<paragraph id="E34236D4BC4FFFDD51E9BA85FB69FB53" blockId="9.[151,1437,909,1404]" pageId="9" pageNumber="32">
Type data: Two females were found at 
<collectionCode id="85ECAE11BC4FFFDD5331BA86FD04FC33" box="[591,697,909,935]" pageId="9" pageNumber="32">OUMNH</collectionCode>
with original Lepeletier’s labels of identification and provenance (“Cay”= Cayenne). Although 
<bibRefCitation id="876C4B25BC4FFFDD5091BABAFD08FC5F" author="Lepeletier, A. L. M." box="[495,693,945,971]" pageId="9" pageNumber="32" refId="ref10183" refString="Lepeletier, A. L. M. (1841) Histoire Naturelle des Insectes. Hymenopteres. Vol. 2. Roret, Paris, 680 pp." type="book" year="1841">Lepeletier (1841)</bibRefCitation>
